[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering test naming conventions**\n\nI'm thinking that there shouldn't be a dollar sign in test names. Should helper classes be inner classes? It seems like avoiding named inner classes in H2 class names would be wise. If inner classes reflect config with a dollar sign, then the file name might be fine. The rules around naming test classes for inner classes are tricky. Using public static inner helper classes is possible, but it might be better to just stick to top-level package-private helper classes in the same file.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0d060983c6be814e0169f7bdc78f3c81908f4965137d5a9f72\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp973YfPBZ90JRPCItrAv4E0eciaBb_nYNPNJ6xwhwTnnYfhWB_y2Vy1EaO-iXe5Ph5UTcFefBmKpBVDj99uwv4mj7LL91mL6kMjhHHS1-WtwHwNErnUXvSMZEpHfzerP5bmQQgZlFnG3ODmqKpgxzZ2gh86tu0W3vIgN29HS8g_q3SGzoQ8EnOiw0Ri0FVuY9RGq9MLHxu4_jQHCpXArEeFFEQMoY5a_TkRUfaak894TQWeG6GF8T1ToeT0ezRTqOUha9aX-cV3T02IAEu3ebpQ8_Hi6ZYQOPT38Igwdfu9ZlVl0EUSVPuuDKJnoO9HcXcjT0yyDVEskCwF44f4o7Lppxgf4HU1irNrBHFpnwAJ-lLr79gqHJF6gQV83GkpYk5goyy8lXIlTsdF4_MLHe6g0j58K9hErH93xvgvGrixzY7DDgtOapyK9xaTFuOkER7B9YPjEBnJjpeLCllqL5Houj84vZsdvM491JNXSbxCfO5mOe8IkiSwGN5ZMPQaqrquJrEY4n_ZHqCZuFwIKxbxyd8527Q2MLHraGci6aMWlkTymxMSIWT0kHuK2L4XDys28dgr8PBXB-Pfy44U10KLOnObEUqcH1CV6cZveVz-j7YoxB7KIbwGGZDDdwdQqLIFw7tZmakiU1IyZ_4iKFG5A4uCWXA3EFNI1JH_iH5l7RzVwilsD-hUYDyS4CUP3K9cX2yIjbnpOzgF2UcoAm6HRGXEBcg5tFbAYf-tjWnFH7dbsoUgZa58nk-Kds7s3ae5yg5DG0M-a-Nv7lLYd8uNFyiz4Ir9hMFz_mZmj-gQCqRmY_3i1_ZLHkXemMlaMZPY84f06vZIlJn7nvZMvxBLmy5TFeVCAk54FnmGC-5YaDrmbQr-3j0uZHndE1mt3rRiLcRUYDPzcdJUbRsnkI1dmmibfGDbSGvb4hi4UgT5GiFBoLiIblDv9_NWfC4q417b_kgYGspfUMQG_wUDelZkUxKlyMAWmMpjUSfbQZ6hSJcZmHe0tz8cVUsIhTR-yHG9nS8q_CueNk0biAbv4AM3Pir0XJfl0uN_5YeYqrAq9iWR8zgnzJ4gIVpCaT_zM71_BRVW3-VNoUH-VrqI5QMX7NeH1umsnUo50HmIDke6BjHvE1Up7x8YH3BS14TT75dxvv-7t2MaRrX9kUZKSldypQvAGIMHpMdSIrMViXywY6ajX1xdiaQ75KQ5r-oH